body_html:
I'm very interested in solving this problem for you.

The log you shared above doesn't include Bazel progress messages. Could you run:

./configure
bazel clean --expunge
bazel fetch //tensorflow/... |& tee log.txt

And then attach log.txt to this issue?

Also would you mind running the following commands and sharing their output?

curl -I http://bazel-mirror.storage.googleapis.com/raw.githubusercontent.com/waylonflinn/weblas/v0.9.0/dist/weblas.js
curl -I https://raw.githubusercontent.com/waylonflinn/weblas/v0.9.0/dist/weblas.js

I'm very interested in solving this problem for you.

The log you shared above doesn't include Bazel progress messages. Could you run:

```sh
./configure
bazel clean --expunge
bazel fetch //tensorflow/... |& tee log.txt
```

And then attach log.txt to this issue?

Also would you mind running the following commands and sharing their output?

```sh
curl -I http://bazel-mirror.storage.googleapis.com/raw.githubusercontent.com/waylonflinn/weblas/v0.9.0/dist/weblas.js
curl -I https://raw.githubusercontent.com/waylonflinn/weblas/v0.9.0/dist/weblas.js
```
